name: ExtensionGoal_Target
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.Goal.target` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `Goal.target` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `Goal.target` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`Goal.target` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `Goal.target` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `Goal.target` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `Goal.target` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `Goal.target` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `Goal.target`, but has no comparisons.

element.short: The target value to be achieved
element.definition: The target value of the focus to be achieved to signify the fulfillment of the goal, e.g. 150 pounds, 7.0%. Either the high or low or both values of the range can be specified. Similarly, if the high value is missing, it indicates that the goal is achieved at any focus value at or above the low value.
